```json
{
  "application": "SLURM",
  "details": {
    "job_name": "cnn-extr_onep-wind",
    "nodes": 1,
    "tasks_per_node": 1,
    "cpus_per_task": 10,
    "memory_per_cpu": "5GB",
    "time": "01:00:00",
    "account": "process2",
    "partition": "plgrid-testing",
    "array": "0-4",
    "modules": [
      "plgrid/tools/python/2.7.14",
      "plgrid/libs/openslide/3.4.1"
    ],
    "environment": {
      "HOME": "$PLG_USER_STORAGE",
      "SCRATCH": "$PLG_USER_SCRATCH",
      "PLG_USER_SCRATCH_SHARED": "$PLG_USER_SCRATCH_SHARED",
      "PLG_GROUPS_STORAGE": "$PLG_GROUPS_STORAGE",
      "PLG_GROUPS_SHARED": "$PLG_GROUPS_SHARED",
      "PYTHONPATH": "${HOME}/projects/EnhanceR/${PROJECT}/code/${PROJECT}/lib/python2.7",
      "PROCESS_UC1__HAS_SKIMAGE_VIEW": "",
      "PROCESS_UC1__HAS_TENSORFLOW": ""
    },
    "script_purpose": "CNN runner for SLURM with one patient/process (or patient/CPU) plus mask window sweep (linear sampling) per patient.",
    "data_dir": "${DATA_DIR}/lesion_annotations/",
    "results_dir": "${RESULTS_DIR}",
    "command": "cnn --config-file=${CONF_DIR}/config.${SLURM_JOB_NAME}.ini --results-dir=${results_dir} --log-level=debug --patients=${patient} --seed=0 --method=linear --window ${win_start} ${win_end} extract"
  }
}
```
